verbs.description: resonate (third-person singular simple present resonates, present participle resonating, simple past and past participle resonated)

entries.meaning: To vibrate or sound, especially in response to another vibration.
examples: The books on top of the piano resonate when he plays certain notes.

entries.meaning: (figurative) To have an effect or impact; to influence; to engender support.
examples: His words resonated with the crowd.
